also Is it possible to have everyone in the group target one monster without having to re do it every round<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utarissadr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarissa DR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 9:43:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardy 8</span><hr size=1> Hit a number corresponding to the character they are and hit L.  I don't think orders repeat except attack/def/protect/berserk, etc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 9:48:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=34>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardy 8</span><hr size=1> Out of curiosity, at what point can your thief reliably steal things from stores?<br>
<br>
We're  around level 6 or 7 or so, and I didn't quite keep my pickpocket maxed - it's in the mid 20s.  At what point will I be able to reliably steal things like spellbooks and such? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=homerj>HomerJ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 3:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardy 8</span><hr size=1> ok i have a question about changing classes.  what does it do? hahahah  will i lose my skills from my first class or do i keep them and then develop the new class' skills?  so if i start as a wizard then at level  change to a warrior, can i cast spells still? also will i get the benifits of the extra hp's of a warrior? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ullabaktharr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llabak Tharr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 3:09:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardy 8</span><hr size=1> You will lose the special abilities of the mage when you switch to fighter, and will lose the ability to gain extra spells (your book will grey out).  <br>
<br>
However any spells you already had learned you can continue to use, and you can still gain skill in that spell realm.<br>
<br>
My bard spent a level as a psionicist, so he has some mind blast spell or something, and gets skill increases in it, he's just not able to get any more spells in that field.<br>
<br>
I don't think he'll get HPs retroactively though.<br>
<br>
Also, they have to have the min stats for the other skill.  I thought about changing my bard into a samurai, or some other tank, but he doesn't meet the min stats <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukoru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Koru</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 3:14:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizardy 8</span><hr size=1> It takes a while until you can steal the more expensive items reliably. I think it was around 50-60 skill my rogue started to have decent chances of getting spell books and equiv. Just keep practicing on cheap items, they're a lot easier to steal then expensive ones. Also some people are harder to steal from than others.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure I'd recommend doing a lot of class switching. You don't lose the skills upon changing but you also can't improve them if your new class doesn't get those skills. Same for spells, you start as a wizard then change to warrior you'll only have the wizard spells you had and will never get any better at them. I'm sure one of the others can explain in better detail. As for me though, I don't do class switching, unlike Wiz7 it just isn't worth it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udraqq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draqq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 12:33:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5914.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Superman Spell = UBER</span><hr size=1> Does anyone else use the spell Superman?<br>
<br>
When casting this spell on an ally it increases dex/spd and AC.  Casting at level 4 or 5 power gives a boost of 20 to dex and spd.  <br>
